Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to offer for the first time to market for sale via Expressions of Interest, 347 Lytton Road, Morningside. The property represents a rare opportunity to secure a substantial land holding within one of the most highly sought after industrial suburbs of South-East Queensland. Morningside is one of the most tightly held industrial suburbs offering easy  access to the Port of Brisbane, Brisbane CBD and the major arterial networks servicing South-East Queensland. 

This offering provides any astute investor or owner occupier endless opportunities to reposition or redevelop this substantial site. Some of the keys features of this site are:

•	Land Area of approximately 48,814sqm*
•	Building area of approximately 13,317sqm* 
•	Improvements comprise of office accommodation / warehouse / cold storage
•	Two street access (Lytton Road & Barwon Street) 
•	Fully fenced and secured site 
•	Secured income until 30th June 2020 plus options
•	Annual income of $1,500,000 + outgoings + GST (triple net lease)
•	Ripe for repositioning or redevelopment


For Sale via Expressions of Interest closing Wednesday 27th February 2019 at 4pm.

For further information regarding this rare opportunity or to arrange your inspection, please contact the Exclusive Agents below.

CBRE is excited to present to the market for sale Unit 4/185 Beverley Street, Morningside. Morningside is situated approx. 6 radial kilometres south east of the Brisbane CBD and enjoys close proximity to the Port precinct and Gateway Arterial which offers easy access to north and south coast arterials. Morningside offers close proximity to transport services and shopping facilities whilst being centrally located within the prime Gateway Industrial Precinct.

4/185 Beverley Street, Morningside is a modern, tilt panel industrial unit boasting huge main road exposure to Lytton Road. Currently set up as a wholesale coffee operation with a fully approved café & commercial kitchen; this is an opportunity not to be missed! Some of the features of this investment include:

•	Total floor area of 226sqm - office/warehouse/retail/café & kitchen
•	Opportunity to purchase as an investment with a lease in place or purchase building and business together
•	Unit offers huge exposure to main Lytton Road generating significant business opportunity
•	Fully set up as a wholesale coffee operation with a fully approved café & commercial kitchen

4/185 Beverley Street, Morningside is being offered for sale via Expressions of Interest closing 9th September 2020 at 4pm.

For further information surrounding this unique investment opportunity, please contact Exclusive Agent, Ben Lyons of CBRE today!

- 40sqm of office apace
- Surrounded by quality tenants
- Close to the city

Modern office in a sought after precinct. The property is in a prime location approximately 5 km east of the Brisbane CBD with good access to the gateway arterial network.

Located in the highly sought after area of Morningside, this property is well positioned just off Lytton Road. The subject site is approx. 6 kilometres south east of the Brisbane CBD and is within close proximity to the Gateway Motorway and Oxford Street precinct.

For more information or to arrange your inspection, please contact the Exclusive Agents Ben Lyons or Tim Langford from CBRE

The property features the following: 

+	37sqm* mezzanine office

This quality industrial unit can be bought vacant possession or with a lease in place. For further information or to arrange your inspection, please contact Exclusive Agent Ben Lyons of CBRE.

CBRE is pleased to offer a substantial Brisbane Food Grade Portfolio to the market.The portfolio provides the opportunity to acquire in Australia’s rapidly growing cold storage and logistics markets. Consisting of 4 cold storage and food grade logistics facilities in key Brisbane precincts; the Portfolio is offered fully leased to Visco Foods, Priestley’s Gourmet Delights, Lago Cold Stores and Artisan Food Co Australia.

- Situated within core Brisbane precincts
- Fixed annual growth of between 3.0% and 3.5%
- Total GLA of 13,078 sqm
- Total Site Area of 26,592 sqm

The Brisbane Food Grade Portfolio is offered for sale via Expressions of Interest closing Friday 9th April 2021 at 12:00pm AEST.
